      • findCommand

        public java.util.Optional<CommandCallable> findCommand(@Nonnull
                                                       java.util.List<CommandCallable> commands,
                                                       @Nonnull
                                                       java.lang.String[] input,
                                                       boolean isLabelIgnoreCase)
        Attempts to find the CommandCallable that is mapped to a label which is generated through the input.

        This command mapper supports aliases as well as a feature called command shortening. Command shortening essentially means that the input doesn't need to be equals to the label. Instead it is sufficient if the input starts with the label. For instance if the label is foo, then f, fo and foo are all valid input. If more then one command can be mapped the command mapping fails.

        Parameters:
        commands - the List of CommandCallables to search through
        input - the input to build the labels from
        isLabelIgnoreCase - true if the case of the input should be ignored
        Returns:
        an Optional describing the matching CommandCallable or an empty Optional if no command was found.
